  16 Sep 2012; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> ruby-bz2-0.2.2-r1.ebuild:
  Convert to EAPI 4; add ree18, document lack of other targets.

*ruby-bz2-0.2.2-r1 (28 Jan 2010)

  28 Jan 2010; Diego E. Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  -ruby-bz2-0.2.2.ebuild, +ruby-bz2-0.2.2-r1.ebuild:
  Replace ebuild with a ruby-ng one, only support Ruby 1.8 as that's the
  only version supported. Closes bug #292275.

  09 May 2009; Diego E. Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  ruby-bz2-0.2.2.ebuild:
  Avoid building for Ruby 1.9.

  18 Jun 2006; Andrej Kacian <ticho@gentoo.org> ruby-bz2-0.2.2.ebuild:
  Marked ~x86, as requested in bug #136894 by Josip Dzolonga <jdzolonga at
  gmail.com>.

*ruby-bz2-0.2.2 (15 Jun 2006)

  15 Jun 2006; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org> +metadata.xml,
  +ruby-bz2-0.2.2.ebuild:
  Initial import, requested by Jon Hood (squinky86) in bug #136204, loosely
  based on work by Josip Dzolonga in the same bug.

